  "text": "Environment stochasticity. A lot of work in section 4.1 (related to exploration problem) create their reward with prediction error instead of the improvement of prediction error (see §7.2 for a thorough analysis). This discrepancy explains the difficulty of several works to handle the whitenoise effect [CITATION_1] or, more generally, to handle the stochasticity of the environment. Some articles from the state of the art handle this issue (see table 3 ), but each of them has drawbacks:",
